file=Brand Studio/lena/operational/tool/lena-tool-requirements.md · h=name: lena-tool-requirements\ntype: operational/tool\nstatus: derived directly from instructions in each skill file\nassigned_agent: lena (Brand Studio / Brand Voice)\ndate_added: 2026-07-07\n · p:=What each of lena's skills technically needs.\n\n**This file specifies needs — it does not grant them.** Actual access is a separate runtime-configuration step wherever lena is deployed; this table is the checklist for whoever configures it.\n · tb=\| Skill \| Required \| Optional / Future \| Source line \| · tb=\|---\|---\|---\|---\| · tb=\| voice-guides \| File read (voice-guide file); file append (override log) \| — \| Phase 1 load; Phase 4 flag/log \| · tb=\| copywriting \| None beyond conversation \| — \| "Prerequisites: None" (source's own line) \| · tb=\| email-marketer \| File write (sequence packages) \| Email/ESP connector for send + engagement metrics readback \| Output format; deliverability diagnostics need real metrics \| · tb=\| humanic-writing \| File read (voice guide, assets: tells catalog + archetypes) \| — \| Phase 1 sources \| · n:=- Lena is deliberately light: no scripts, no Python. Her leverage is text craft against written guides.\n- The email connector is the one integration that changes lena's ceiling — without it she designs sequences; with it (plus kai's metrics) deliverability diagnostics use real engagement data instead of operator-reported symptoms.\n- No web search — OS-level layer, as everywhere.\n · h:to Apply=File read on guide/asset paths + file write for packages is the floor.\n